## Review Rules for `megapolis-api`

## Checklist
Create a proper checklist and then go through each item.

- Ask the user to provide a summary of the feature in detail.
- Check what db changes were made. In `app/models` and `alembic` folders.
  - Check if the db changes are necessary.
- Check what new endpoints were added. In `app/routes` folder.
  - Check if the endpoints are justified and minimal.
- Check what new services were added. In `app/services` folder.
  - Check if the services are implemented correctly.
- Check what new dependencies were added. In `pyproject.toml` file.
  - Check if the dependencies are necessary.
- Check what new utils were added. In `app/utils` folder.
- When in review check if there is a better way to do something or approach the problem.
- Check if naming conventions are followed.


**Go through all the changed files and complete the checklist for each and every file.**